              {
                type: "paragraph",
                text:
                  "Finding the right rate of speech, depending on the situations you are in can help ensure clear and effective communication."
              },
              {
                type: "list",
                text: [
                  "Aim for a conversational pace, where you use a mix of fast and slow speeds.",
                  "You can speak quickly to show excitement, urgency, or strong emotions, and speak slowly to emphasise important points or help the audience understand new ideas."
                ]
              },
              {
                type: "TextTitle",
                text: "For example,"
              },
              {
                type: "list",
                text: [
                  "A news anchor speaking at a moderate pace so that viewers can understand the information being shared easily.",
                  "A stand-up comedian speaking quickly to keep the audience entertained and engaged.",
                  "Your professor speaks slowly during a lecture to help students understand complex concepts.",
                  "A motivational speaker using changes in pace to keep the audience interested and excited.",
                  "A customer service representative speaks slowly and clearly to ensure that customers can follow instructions and get the help they need."
                ]
              },
